dapting their own identities to the changing political conditions they encountered. Through a trove of diplomatic and mercantile letters, inquisitorial records, literary texts, marginalia, and visual material, The Refugee-Diplomat recovers the agency of religious refugees in international affairs, revealing their profound impact on the emergence of early modern diplomatic culture and practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aDiplomacyxHistoryy16th century. 0aProtestantszItalyzVenicexHistoryy16th century. 0aReligious refugeeszItalyzVenicexHistoryy16th century. 4aDiplomatic History. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aHISTORY / Renaissance.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package 2018z978311066747908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell Univ. Press eBook-Package Pilot Project 2018z978311060655308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishz978311060403008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018z9783110603149oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501715334423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501715334.jpg  a978-3-11-060403-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060655-3  Cornell Univ. Press eBook-Package Pilot Project 2018b2018  a978-3-11-066747-9  COR eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SS